      • get

        public scala.concurrent.Future<java.io.File> get(java.lang.String id,
                                                 java.io.File file)
        Downloads the file with the given id from the server and saves it to the given file. Once the file is downloaded, the content is validated against the SHA-1 id.
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the file to get (SHA-1 hash of the contents)
        file - the local file in which to store the contents returned from the server
        Returns:
        a future containing the file, if successful, or the exception if there was an error

      • post

        public scala.concurrent.Future<java.lang.String> post(java.io.File file)
        Uploads the given file to the server, storing it under the given SHA-1 hash of the contents.
        Parameters:
        file - the local file to upload to the server
        Returns:
        a future containing the file id (SHA-1), if successful, or the exception if there was an error

      • head

        public scala.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Object> head(java.lang.String id)
        Checks the existence of the file with the given id on the server
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the file to check (SHA-1 hash of the contents)
        Returns:
        a future boolean indicating the existence of the file, if successful, or the exception if there was an HTTP error

      • delete

        public scala.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Object> delete(java.lang.String id)
        Deletes the file with the given id on the server (Should normally only be used in tests).
        Parameters:
        id - the id of the file to delete (SHA-1 hash of the contents)
        Returns:
        a future boolean: true if the file could be deleted or did not exist, or the exception if the file could not be deleted or there was an HTTP error
